However, women view divorce as a self-destructive course that will dent the reputation of them quickly and leave no one willing to set up reasonable standards of courtship with them. In view of their willingness to repudiate each other after the first wrangle, Belizean men terminate their marriages twice in their lives. This only leaves women to assume the extreme traditional views of Belizean society about them. The differences between the gender egalitarianistic way of approaching life and the traditional cultural values toward the opposition of divorce are fatal for marriages among young native men and foreign women. When the marriages fail, mostly foreign women do not seek to hire lawyers in order to fight for alimony or other compensations. They are more involved in moving to some other countries where they can realize the opportunities to marry new, more acceptable partners instead of wasting monetary resources over and over by litigation.

“The most successful marriage is one in which you continue to do all the things you did before, just more of them. ”
